39. Financial risk management (continued)

Offsetting ﬁnancial assets and ﬁnancial liabilities

The Group reports financial assets and ﬁnancial liabilities on a net basis on the statement of financial position where there Is a legally enforceable right to offset the recognised amounts and there is an Intention to settle on a net basis or to realise the asset and settle the liabilities simultaneously.
